INSERT INTO items VALUES(76,1028,483,'ECON_DEV_COMM','ID 16-081','ECON_DEV_COMM ZONE_USE_COMM ECON_DEV_REDEV The first choice, `ECON_DEV_COMM` (Community-based economic development efforts aimed at improving local commerce and business districts), was made because the agenda item is a presentation focused on a "Commercial Business District." This suggests an emphasis on economic development within a particular commercial area, aligning well with initiatives that aim to enhance business districts and local commerce. The mention of "The Hemingway District" specifically points towards a community-focused effort in a predefined commercial area, which is typical of the `ECON_DEV_COMM` classification.','D. ID 16-081 Commercial Business District Presentation - Jim August President The Hemingway District','2c2dd580-e71f-47a9-a916-27cacd7e1d0c',7,'2024-10-28T01:59:44','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('D. ID 16-081 Commercial Business District Presentation - Jim August President The\nHemingway District\nJim August, owner of The Irish Shop and President of the Hemingway Business District\ngave a presentation that described various aspects of the district, a mix of comercial\nretail and entertainment venues.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(77,1511,29,'PROC','ID 16-157','``` PROC_ELECTIONS PROC_BOARD_RULES STAFF_MGMT_HIRE ``` The first choice, `PROC_ELECTIONS`, was selected because the agenda item pertains to a "Board and Commission Vacancy Report," which is closely related to municipal elections and appointments. These processes typically involve the management of vacancies within various boards and commissions, as well as potential new appointments to fill those positions. Therefore, the heading and date reference suggests that it''s part of the electoral process management.','E. ID 16-157 Board and Commission Vacancy Report for May 16, 2016.','8a78db7f-3f63-40e7-9cdc-18c15741294f',7,'2024-10-28T01:59:44','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('E. ID 16-157 Board and Commission Vacancy Report for May 16, 2016.\nThere were no comments.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(78,1540,78,'PROC','MOT 16-062','PROC_ELECTIONS STAFF_MGMT_HIRE PUB_ENG_CITIZEN The agenda item involves the appointment of individuals to various commissions and boards, which is directly related to municipal governance and the electoral process. The appointing of individuals to commissions and boards typically falls under PROC_ELECTIONS, as such appointments are part of managing municipal offices and the electoral process within the village government structure. The selection and approval of board and commission members align with the appointment processes overseen by municipal governments.','F. MOT 16-062 Motion to consent to the Village President''s Appointment of: Building Codes Advisory Commission, Christopher Hamer, Member Board of Health: Dhana Ganesan, Member Citizen Involvement Commission: Erika Washington, Member Historic Preservation C','e6c7d21f-3262-48a4-8edb-75fc47639b23',7,'2024-10-28T01:59:44','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('F. MOT 16-062 Motion to consent to the Village President’s Appointment of:\nBuilding Codes Advisory Commission, Christopher Hamer, Member\nBoard of Health: Dhana Ganesan, Member\nCitizen Involvement Commission: Erika Washington, Member\nHistoric Preservation Commission: Aleksandra Tadic, Member\nMadison Street Coalition: Nick Solomos, Appoint as Member\nMadison Street Coalition: Robert Spadoni, Appoint as Member\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Tucker, seconded by Village Trustee Barber,\nthat this Motion be approved. The motion was approved. The roll call on the\nvote was as follows:\nAYES: 6 - Village Trustee Barber, Village Trustee Button Ott, Village Trustee Lueck, Village\nTrustee Salzman, Village Trustee Tucker, and Village President Abu-Taleb\nNAYS: 0\nABSENT: 1 - Village Trustee Brewer\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
