INSERT INTO items VALUES(500,3225,1627,'ENV_SUS_ENERGY','ID 20-284','ENV_SUS_ENERGY SUS_ENE_RENEW ENV_SUS_CLIM The chosen classification, ENV_SUS_ENERGY, is primarily because the agenda item is focused on sustainability projects, specifically relating to energy and energy benchmarking. The mention of "Energy Benchmarking with Energy Star Portfolio Manager" directly relates to the idea of energy efficiency projects and measuring energy performance, which fits well under the category of environmental impact reduction through energy initiatives. The agenda item''s focus on a "Greenhouse Gas Inventory Update" also aligns with evaluating energy consumption patterns and striving towards more sustainable energy use, supporting this classification choice.','M. ID 20-284 Report on the Metropolitan Mayors Caucus'' Greenest Region Corps Fellow Sustainability Projects: Greenhouse Gas Inventory Update and Energy Benchmarking with Energy Star Portfolio Manager','bbc4e30e-0b93-4f19-ada2-ea847806a264',44,'2024-10-28T01:59:44','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('M. ID 20-284 Report on the Metropolitan Mayors Caucus’ Greenest Region Corps Fellow\nSustainability Projects: Greenhouse Gas Inventory Update and Energy\nBenchmarking with Energy Star Portfolio Manager\nEnvironmental Sustainability Coordinator Mindy Agnew presented a report on\nthe "Sustainability Projects: Greenhouse Gas Inventory Update and Energy\nBenchmarking with Energy Star Portfolio Manager". The report was created by\nthe Metropolitan Mayors Caucus’ Greenest Region Corps Fellow, Leslie\nHernandez. This report provides top-level examples of the collected data.\nRecommendations will come at a later time.\nVillage Trustee Boutet, Village Trustee Walker-Peddakotla, and Village Trustee\nMoroney each expressed their appreciation for the Village’s work and look\nforward to the next steps.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
