INSERT INTO items VALUES(553,3359,19,'PROC','ORD 16-106','PROC_ORD_RULES FIN_MGT_BUDGET STAFF_MGMT_COMP The first choice, PROC_ORD_RULES, is selected because the agenda item is about the second reading and adoption of an ordinance. Ordinances are typically classified under procedural or rules-related categories, as they involve changes to municipal laws. This fits within the PROC_ORD_RULES category, which encompasses ordinance and procedural rules related to the adoption, modification, and repeal of municipal laws, making it the most accurate match for the agenda item provided.','G. ORD 16-106 Second Reading and Adoption of an Ordinance Amending Chapter 2 ("Administration"), Article 6 ("Finance Department") of the Oak Park Village Code by Adding a new Section 2-6-20 ("Living Wage")','490102c3-a706-4488-89b3-015f48eab147',48,'2024-10-28T01:59:44','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('G. ORD 16-106 Second Reading and Adoption of an Ordinance Amending Chapter 2\n(“Administration”), Article 6 (“Finance Department”) of the Oak Park\nVillage Code by Adding a new Section 2-6-20 (“Living Wage”)\nVillage Trustee Barber commented that at the First Reading, it was noted that the added\ncost to bring certain contractors up to $12 per hour would be passed on to the Village. He\nasked how this will impact the Village''s annual budget.\nVillage Manager Pavlicek stated that competitive bids on contracts being awarded for\n2017 have been completed prior to the adoption of this ordinance. It will not have any\nimpact on the Village until late 2017, when those contracts come up for 2018. She\nestimated that the parking garage security contract will increase by approximately\n$40,000.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Tucker, seconded by Village Trustee Lueck, that\nthis Ordinance be adopted. The motion was approved. The roll call on the vote\nwas as follows:\nAYES: 7 - Village Trustee Barber, Village Trustee Brewer, Village Trustee Button Ott, Village\nTrustee Lueck, Village Trustee Salzman, Village Trustee Tucker, and Village\nPresident Abu-Taleb\nNAYS: 0\nABSENT: 0\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
