INSERT INTO items VALUES(642,2147,187,'TRANS_INF_TRAFFIC','ORD 15-187','TRANS_INF_TRAFFIC TRANS_INF_PARK PROC_ORD_RULES The first choice, TRANS_INF_TRAFFIC, was made because the agenda item involves the amendment of village code related to motor vehicles and traffic, specifically concerning fines and penalties for traffic, parking, and vehicle license violations. This directly aligns with traffic-related issues, which include regulations, safety measures, and changes in traffic policies as described in the TRANS_INF_TRAFFIC classification.','E. ORD 15-187 First Reading of an Ordinance Amending Chapter 15 ("Motor Vehicles and Traffic"), Article 5 ("Schedule of Fines and Penalties for Certain Minor Traffic Violation, Parking and Vehicle License Violations") of the Oak Park Village Code as Review','2d63148b-d4b0-4774-b23a-c7a10d30439e',56,'2024-10-28T01:59:44','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('E. ORD 15-187 First Reading of an Ordinance Amending Chapter 15 (“Motor Vehicles and\nTraffic”), Article 5 (“Schedule of Fines and Penalties for Certain Minor\nTraffic Violation, Parking and Vehicle License Violations”) of the Oak Park\nVillage Code as Reviewed by the Finance Committee of the Village Board at\nits October 22, 2015 Meeting\nVillage Manager Pavlicek stated that this Ordinance is in regards to parking citation fines.\nThese were last reviewed in 2008; most fees will increase by $10. The increase will be\nmore substantial in terms of handicap placards, as the Village is currently out of\ncompliance with the State.\nChief Financial Officer Craig Lesner discussed the volume of citations and stated that\nprojected revenue is $354,000.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
