INSERT INTO items VALUES(644,2879,64,'ENV_SUS_PLST','ORD 15-200','ENV_SUS_PLST ENV_SUS_CLIM ENV_SUS_ENERGY The agenda item provided relates to a new environmental fee, which indicates a focus on sustainability and environmentally related economic measures. The first choice, ENV_SUS_PLST, was made because environmental fees often aim at reducing or managing environmental issues, such as plastic use. While it''s possible the environmental fee doesn''t directly reference plastics, regulations of this nature frequently include plastic reduction measures. However, without specific mention of plastic in the ordinance title, the choice is based on this common association.','G. ORD 15-200 First Reading of An Ordinance Amending Section 20-7-2 of the Oak Park Village Code to Establish New Environmental Fee Rates','cfc9944e-2617-494e-be4b-1dc0bef61f72',56,'2024-10-28T01:59:44','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('G. ORD 15-200 First Reading of An Ordinance Amending Section 20-7-2 of the Oak Park\nVillage Code to Establish New Environmental Fee Rates\nVillage Manager Pavlicek stated that this is a 3.5% increase to incorporate costs that\nthe Village incurred through the contract with Waste Management in 2015 for the cost of\nresidential solid waste collection. The additional half percent is for anticipated increases\nin disposal costs at the landfill. These were not passed on to residents in 2015, but staff\nwould like to keep pace with the current cost of the service.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(645,2943,68,'ZONE_USE_AMEND','ORD 15-195','ZONE_USE_AMEND TRANS_INF_PARK PUB_WRK_PARK The first choice, ZONE_USE_AMEND, was selected because the agenda item involves amending an ordinance related to parking permit fees. While it is specifically focused on motor vehicle regulations, the act of amending the ordinance suggests a change in the zoning or use regulations as they pertain to parking permits. This aligns with ZONE_USE_AMEND, which covers changes and updates to zoning ordinances, including those that could affect business operations and land use, such as parking provisions in the village code.','H. ORD 15-195 Second Reading and Adoption of an Ordinance Amending Parking Permit Fees as Set Forth in Chapter 15 ("Motor Vehicles and Traffic") of the Oak Park Village Code','e14ce848-baf7-4939-a975-75c894b7959e',56,'2024-10-28T01:59:44','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('H. ORD 15-195 Second Reading and Adoption of an Ordinance Amending Parking Permit\nFees as Set Forth in Chapter 15 (“Motor Vehicles and Traffic”) of the Oak\nPark Village Code\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Salzman, seconded by Village Trustee Ott, that\nthis Ordinance be adopted. The motion was approved. The roll call on the vote\nwas as follows:\nAYES: 5 - Village Trustee Brewer, Village Trustee Lueck, Village Trustee Ott, Village Trustee\nSalzman, and Village President Abu-Taleb\nNAYS: 0\nABSENT: 2 - Village Trustee Barber, and Village Trustee Tucker\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
