INSERT INTO items VALUES(1136,277,355,'ZONE_USE_COMM','ORD 15-085','ZONE_USE_COMM ECON_DEV_REDEV ZONE_USE_AMEND The agenda item refers to an ordinance authorizing the purchase and lease of real property located in the village, which directly ties to zoning and land use issues. The category ZONE_USE_COMM is the best fit as it deals with commercial zoning matters, including permits and developments. Given that the purchase and lease of property are typically aligned with commercial zoning considerations, especially concerning location and future use within the municipality, this category is the most applicable. Additionally, purchasing real property may imply potential development or commercial utilization, further justifying this classification.','A. ORD 15-085 An Ordinance Authorizing the Purchase and Lease of Certain Real Property Located at 932-946 Madison Street in the Village of Oak Park.','718fc00d-52ec-49f2-bd7f-436e449600d8',97,'2024-10-28T01:59:44','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('A. ORD 15-085 An Ordinance Authorizing the Purchase and Lease of Certain Real Property\nLocated at 932-946 Madison Street in the Village of Oak Park.\nVillage Manager Pavlicek noted that the District 97 Administrative Building will\nbecome the Village''s property later this year per an intergovernmental\nagreement approved in 2014. The Village feels that since the adjacent\nRobinson''s Ribs property is actively on the market, it should be acquired and\ncombined with the D-97 property as part of the redevelopment of Madison\nStreet. The purchase price is within the range of the appraised value of the\nproperty. Robinson''s will lease the premises through November of 2015; then\nthe Village will begin to actively market the property.\nThere was a brief discussion.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Brewer, seconded by Village Trustee Tucker,\nthat this Ordinance be adopted. The motion was approved. The roll call on the\nvote was as follows:\nAYES: 6 - Village Trustee Barber, Village Trustee Brewer, Village Trustee Ott, Village Trustee\nSalzman, Village Trustee Tucker, and Village President Abu-Taleb\nNAYS: 0\nABSENT: 1 - Village Trustee Lueck\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
