INSERT INTO items VALUES(1708,1658,172,'PROC','ID 17-597','PROC_TRANSPAR PUB_ENG_PROC PROC_PUBLIC_INPUT The first choice, "PROC_TRANSPAR," is made because the agenda item involves a proclamation, and one of the key aspects of transparency and open government initiatives is the public declaration or recognition of support for issues, people, or events. Proclamations often aim to foster open communication and increase public awareness, which aligns with transparency goals. In this specific case, the agenda item is a proclamation in support of the City of Charlottesville, which could be seen as an effort to openly express solidarity and transparency about the municipalities'' stance on a particular issue.','C. ID 17-597 Motion to Approve Proclamation in Support of the City of Charlottesville, Virginia','7f3bf0bb-0c1c-4b18-ae4b-c1edf9fcd2cc',146,'2024-10-28T01:59:44','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('C. ID 17-597 Motion to Approve Proclamation in Support of the City of Charlottesville,\nVirginia\nVillage Trustee Tucker read the Proclamation aloud.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Andrews, seconded by Village Trustee Boutet,\nthat this Proclamation be adopted. A voice vote was taken and the motion was\napproved.\n','\n',char(10)),1);
