INSERT INTO items VALUES(1881,1246,230,'PUB_SAFE_COMM','ID 22-103','PUB_SAFE_COMM PUB_ENG_CITIZEN PROC_PUBLIC_INPUT The agenda item "22-103 E. ID 22-103 Community Safety Project Update by Michele Weinzetl, BerryDunn Consulting" fits best under the category PUB_SAFE_COMM due to its explicit focus on a "Community Safety Project Update." The description of PUB_SAFE_COMM encompasses community safety projects and discussions aimed at enhancing public safety and emergency services, which aligns closely with the nature of the agenda item. The involvement of a consulting firm also suggests a structured approach to community safety, making it a strong fit for this category.','E. ID 22-103 Community Safety Project Update by Michele Weinzetl, BerryDunn Consulting','615f15d3-b815-4dcb-9b0a-611c8061c7e5',160,'2024-10-28T01:59:44','2024-11-05T04:39:00',replace('E. ID 22-103 Community Safety Project Update by Michele Weinzetl, BerryDunn\nConsulting\nVillage Manager Kevin Jackson introduced the Item.\nMichele Weinzetl, a consultant with BerryDunn Consulting, then gave an\nupdate on the Community Safety Project. They have done a number of\ninterviews with department staff and community members, have received a\nnumber of responses on the Social Pinpoint Site, and have conducted a\nseries of open forums. They are currently in the middle of the data analysis\nand will be developing recommendations over the next couple of months,\nand expect to have an initial draft report in May. There will then be a period\nof review for staff to give feedback and make adjustments, and the finalized\ndraft will be posted on the Social Pinpoint site for the public to provide\nfeedback. The consultant will include that feedback as part of the final\ndocument and expect that report to be completed around the end of August\nor early September.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
