INSERT INTO items VALUES(2143,2897,168,'FIN_MGT_BUDGET','MOT 16-122','FIN_MGT_BUDGET FIN_MGT_AUDIT FIN_MGT_GRANTS The agenda item primarily involves accepting and reviewing a capital improvement plan, which relates closely to budget discussions. These discussions typically involve planning, allocating, and detailing future expenditures, as well as incorporating recommendations from the village board and finance committee. This focus on financial planning and management aligns it most strongly with the classification of FIN_MGT_BUDGET, which covers budget discussions for various fiscal years, including detailed breakdowns of revenue and expenditures.','R. MOT 16-122 A Motion to Accept the Five Year Capital Improvement Plan (2017-2021) as Reviewed by the Village Board at the October 4, 2016 Meeting Regular Agenda and Incorporating Recommendations of the Finance Committee of the Village Board','f02f8ed3-4111-4d8a-aebc-6f51ba2d8c34',177,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('R. MOT 16-122 A Motion to Accept the Five Year Capital Improvement Plan (2017-2021) as\nReviewed by the Village Board at the October 4, 2016 Meeting Regular\nAgenda and Incorporating Recommendations of the Finance Committee of\nthe Village Board\nVillage Manager Pavlicek stated that the only notable change to the document previously\npresented to the Finance Committee and Village Board is to defer the fiber optic project\nto 2018.\nVillage Trustee Salzman added that while deferring the expense of laying the cable, staff\nand the Civic Information Systems Commission will be actively planning and presenting\nthe Board with options as to how they can replace the system along with maintaining the\ncurrent system to avoid outages.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Tucker, seconded by Village Trustee Salzman,\nthat this Motion be approved. The motion was approved. The roll call on the\nvote was as follows:\nAYES: 6 - Village Trustee Barber, Village Trustee Button Ott, Village Trustee Lueck, Village\nTrustee Salzman, Village Trustee Tucker, and Village President Abu-Taleb\nNAYS: 0\nABSENT: 1 - Village Trustee Brewer\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
