INSERT INTO items VALUES(2322,313,645,'SUS_ENE_CARB','ID 20-087','SUS_ENE_CARB PUB_ENG_PROC ENV_SUS_CLIM The agenda item "Motion to Approve Proclamation Supporting the United States Congress Enacting the Energy Innovation and Carbon Divide Act of 2019" was classified primarily as SUS_ENE_CARB because it involves support for a legislative act related to carbon policy, specifically the Energy Innovation and Carbon Divide Act. This act aligns directly with carbon fee and dividend policies aimed at reducing the carbon footprint, which is captured by the SUS_ENE_CARB symbolic name. This choice is based on the clear reference to legislative action designed to impact carbon emissions, a key aspect of the SUS_ENE_CARB description.','B. ID 20-087 Motion to Approve Proclamation Supporting the United States Congress Enacting the Energy Innovation and Carbon Divide Act of 2019.','47f8f4e6-5c92-4b4c-b580-e350e20daf51',194,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('B. ID 20-087 Motion to Approve Proclamation Supporting the United States Congress\nEnacting the Energy Innovation and Carbon Divide Act of 2019.\nKenneth O''Hare. Mr. O''Hare spoke in support of the the Energy Innovation and Carbon\nDividend Act.\nDoug Burke. Mr. Burke stated that this Bill will greatly impact climate change as well as\nimprove the economy.\nVillage Trustee Andrews read the Proclamation aloud.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Andrews, seconded by Village Trustee Taglia,\nthat this Proclamation be adopted. The motion carried.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(2323,958,247,'PUB_ENG_PROC','ID 20-088','``` PUB_ENG_PROC PUB_ENG_HEAR TRANS_INF_TRANS ``` The primary reason for choosing "PUB_ENG_PROC" as the best fit is that the agenda item involves a proclamation supporting a designation, which aligns with the description of this category involving proclamations that celebrate community involvement and raise public awareness. The agenda item describes a motion to approve a proclamation, which typically acts as a formal recognition or declaration issued by a government body, fitting well with community-focused proclamations highlighted in "PUB_ENG_PROC".','C. ID 20-088 Motion to Approve Proclamation Supporting the designation of Oak Park Conservatory Stop on the CTA Blue Line at Oak Park Avenue.','d3cdb7f6-dd9e-4daa-a526-af4d4c8ccde4',194,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('C. ID 20-088 Motion to Approve Proclamation Supporting the designation of Oak Park\nConservatory Stop on the CTA Blue Line at Oak Park Avenue.\nVillage Trustee Boutet commented that she would like this changed to a Resolution.\nShe read the Resolution aloud.\nMary Kay Monaghan. Ms. Monaghan discussed how renaming this CTA station will\npromote the conservatory.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Andrews, seconded by Village Trustee Taglia,\nthat this Proclamation be adopted. The motion carried.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
