INSERT INTO items VALUES(2433,3426,13,'FIN_MGT_TAX','ID 16-305','FIN_MGT_TAX FIN_MGT_BUDGET PUB_ENG_HEAR The first choice, "FIN_MGT_TAX", was made because the agenda item "16-305 E. ID 16-305 Truth in Taxation Public Hearing for the Proposed Tax Year 2016 Property Tax Levy" specifically involves a "Truth in Taxation Public Hearing" for a "Property Tax Levy." This closely aligns with tax levy ordinances and fiscal management to ensure adequate funding for municipal services, as described in the "FIN_MGT_TAX" symbolic name. The focus on taxation in this context makes it the most appropriate classification.','E. ID 16-305 Truth in Taxation Public Hearing for the Proposed Tax Year 2016 Property Tax Levy','8ab93c19-634b-4532-9683-50f4760910b5',204,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-10-28T01:59:45',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(2434,3439,270,'FIN_MGT_TAX','ORD 16-139','FIN_MGT_TAX PROC_ORD_RULES FIN_MGT_BUDGET The agenda item provided is primarily focused on the first reading of an ordinance related to amending a section of the Oak Park Village Code concerning "Municipal Gas Use Tax." This suggests that the main subject of the item is related to tax regulations or policies within the municipality. Therefore, "FIN_MGT_TAX" is selected as the best fit because it deals with tax levy ordinances and fiscal management, which encompasses changes and amendments to tax-related municipal codes.','F. ORD 16-139 First Reading of an Ordinance Amending Chapter 23A ("Taxes"), Article 7 ("Municipal Gas Use Tax"), Section 23A-7-3 ("Taxes") of the Oak Park Village Code .End Overview The Ordinance amends Section 23A-7-3 of the Oak Park Village Code ("Villag','f7586eed-499e-4fba-ab41-4b68fdbb0885',204,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('F. ORD 16-139 First Reading of an Ordinance Amending Chapter 23A (“Taxes”), Article 7\n(“Municipal Gas Use Tax”), Section 23A-7-3 (“Taxes”) of the Oak Park Village\nCode\n.End\nVillage Manager Pavlicek commented that typically during the first meeting in November,\nstaff presents to the Board any ordinances proposed to modify fees as part of the\nupcoming budget process. Second Readings and final adoptions will be on either\nNovember 21 or December 5.\nThis Item is relative to the Municipal Gas Tax, which has not been reviewed in a number\nof years. It is raising the tax per therm and will be used to support the General Fund.\nVillage Trustee Barber asked what the impact will be to a typical resident. CFO Steve\nDrazner stated that he does not know the exact figure but it would probably be minimal;\nunder $50 per year. Village Manager Pavlicek stated that staff will get that information as\nwell as the impact to a typical business.\nMr. Drazner clarified that only those who use an out of state supplier will only be affected.\nThose using an Illinois supplier such as Nicor are not subject to the tax. Village Trustee\nBarber asked for a list of all gas suppliers in Oak Park and delineate which will be\naffected and which will not as well as the number of customers impacted.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(2435,3709,422,'PUB_WRK_PARK','ORD 16-141','1. PUB_WRK_PARK 2. TRANS_INF_PARK 3. PROC_VILLAGE_RULES The first choice, PUB_WRK_PARK, was made because the agenda item specifically involves the amendment of parking permit fees, which falls under the management of parking systems and parking fee structures. This classification directly correlates with issues regarding parking fee regulations, making it the most appropriate fit based on the information provided.','G. ORD 16-141 First Reading of an Ordinance Amending the Parking Permit Fees set forth in Section 15-3-18 of the Oak Park Village Code','047df794-0877-4f45-b6bc-e095720be431',204,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-10-28T01:59:45',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(2436,4131,254,'FIN_MGT_TAX','ORD 16-140','FIN_MGT_TAX PROC_ORD_RULES ZONE_USE_AMEND The agenda item in question involves the amendment of a municipal ordinance related to the electric utility tax. Therefore, the most fitting category is FIN_MGT_TAX, as this symbolic name directly relates to ordinances and fiscal management concerned with taxes and the management of municipal services funding. This agenda item specifically pertains to a tax ordinance discussion, which aligns it closely with the ''Tax levy ordinances and fiscal management'' description under FIN_MGT_TAX.','H. ORD 16-140 First Reading of an Ordinance Amending Chapter 23A ("Taxes"), Article 9 ("Utility Tax"), Section 23A-9-10 ("Electric Utility Tax") of the Oak Park Village Code .End Overview The Ordinance amends Section 23A-9-10 of the Oak Park Village Code (','68652be1-aa02-41ce-9d82-99937b70f5e8',204,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('H. ORD 16-140 First Reading of an Ordinance Amending Chapter 23A (“Taxes”), Article 9\n(“Utility Tax”), Section 23A-9-10 (“Electric Utility Tax”) of the Oak Park\nVillage Code\n.End\nVillage Manager Pavlicek stated that this ordinance will make the Village''s electric utility\ntax consistent with State Statute.\nVillage Trustee Brewer asked what the estimated $100,000 in revenue is tied to. Mr.\nDrazner replied that it is based on the amount of electricity used. There are several tiers\nand each tier has a different rate. The effect to individual households is minimal. Village\nManager Pavlicek suggested that staff could prepare something similar to the gas tax\nbreakdown. She noted that the amounts in question are tenths of a penny.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(2437,4385,456,'ZONE_USE_AMEND','ORD 16-133','ZONE_USE_AMEND PROC_ORD_RULES ZONE_USE_COMM The agenda item, "First Reading of an Ordinance Establishing the Annual Building and Construction Permit Fees and Zoning Application Fees of the Village of Oak Park," suggests an ordinance that affects zoning applications and construction-related fees. The symbolic name "ZONE_USE_AMEND" was chosen as the best fit because it directly relates to amendments or changes in zoning regulations or permits, which aligns with the intent to establish new fees for zoning applications. Additionally, amendments to zoning regulations are often required to implement changes in fees associated with permit applications, making this classification particularly relevant.','I. ORD 16-133 First Reading of an Ordinance Establishing the Annual Building and Construction Permit Fees and Zoning Application Fees of the Village of Oak Park','fcce546d-fb3b-455e-a164-052671708eef',204,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('I. ORD 16-133 First Reading of an Ordinance Establishing the Annual Building and\nConstruction Permit Fees and Zoning Application Fees of the Village of Oak\nPark\nVillage Manager Pavlicek noted that this Item is not intended to increase revenue. It is a\nrecommended update to construction permit and zoning application fees to reflect the\ncost of providing these services.\nVillage Trustee Lueck commented that it would be helpful to have some sense of how\nmuch revenue is collected per item, as some of them seem to be impossible to monitor.\nFor example, structural work performed outside the house is obvious but something such\nas a homeowner installing drywall inside can go unnoticed. She asked if it makes sense\nto have something on the books that cannot be enforced.\nChief Building Official Steve Cutaia noted that there is also a very detailed ordinance that\nstates what does not require a permit. Village Trustee Lueck added that most residents\ndon''t even know what they need a permit for.\nIn response to Trustee Lueck''s concerns regarding revenue collection, Village Manager\nPavlicek stated that staff may be able to generate some reports to get this information.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(2438,4841,211,'ZONE_USE_AMEND','ORD 16-142','ZONE_USE_AMEND ENV_SUS_RECY PROC_VILLAGE_RULES The first choice, ZONE_USE_AMEND, was selected because the agenda item describes a first reading of an ordinance amending a chapter of the village code. Specifically, it pertains to rates related to collection services, which can be seen as part of regulatory adjustments within municipal codes. Amending codes for such services likely involves zoning or the management of services within designated areas, aligning with the description of zoning ordinance amendments to update regulations.','J. ORD 16-142 First Reading of An Ordinance Amending Chapter 20, Article 7 of the Oak Park Village Code Regarding Rates for Garbage, Refuse, Yard Waste and Recyclable Materials Collection Services','5fc1527e-8a90-4444-85ca-27f6d391abd9',204,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-10-28T01:59:45',NULL,NULL);
