INSERT INTO items VALUES(2632,1127,54,'PROC','MOT 15-048','PROC_ELECTIONS PROC_BOARD_RULES STAFF_MGMT_HIRE The first choice, "PROC_ELECTIONS," seems most appropriate because the agenda item is about appointments to various commissions. While it doesn''t directly involve municipal elections, appointments to advisory positions often fall within the broader category of election and appointment management. These roles are typically filled through processes managed by municipal leaders, which align well with the considerations of election and appointment processes covered by "PROC_ELECTIONS."','I. MOT 15-048 Motion to consent to the Village President''s Appointment of: Building Codes Advisory Commission - Rick Sabatino, Appoint as Member Disability Access Commission - Leo Irakliotis, Reappoint as Member Farmers Market Commission - Todd Kuna, Appoi','46134aea-1cf4-4742-84ec-20489f6cc07a',218,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('I. MOT 15-048 Motion to consent to the Village President’s Appointment of:\nBuilding Codes Advisory Commission - Rick Sabatino, Appoint as Member\nDisability Access Commission - Leo Irakliotis, Reappoint as Member\nFarmers Market Commission - Todd Kuna, Appoint as Member\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Tucker, seconded by Village Trustee Ott, that\nthis Motion be approved. The motion was approved. The roll call on the vote\nwas as follows:\nAYES: 5 - Village Trustee Brewer, Village Trustee Ott, Village Trustee Salzman, Village\nTrustee Tucker, and Village President Abu-Taleb\nNAYS: 0\nABSENT: 2 - Village Trustee Barber, and Village Trustee Lueck\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(2633,1181,109,'ZONE_USE_AMEND','ORD 15-081','ZONE_USE_AMEND PROC_ORD_RULES PROC_VILLAGE_RULES The first choice, ZONE_USE_AMEND, was selected because the agenda item pertains to amending a part of the Village Code related to building and zoning, which directly involves changes to zoning ordinances, especially concerning the imposition of permit and zoning application fees. This aligns closely with the classification of zoning ordinance amendments.','J. ORD 15-081 First Reading of an Ordinance Amending Chapter 7 ("Buildings"), Article 8 ("Fees") of the Oak Park Village Code to Establish an Annual Building and Construction Permit Fees and Zoning Application Fees Ordinance Requirement.','e5c7871c-3c58-4888-963b-3c17cbf58f0e',218,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-10-28T01:59:45',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(2634,1290,403,'PROC','ORD 15-080','PROC_ORD_RULES FIN_MGT_BUDGET ZONE_USE_AMEND The agenda item "First Reading of an Ordinance Establishing the Annual Building and Construction Permit Fees and Zoning Application Fees of the Village of Oak Park" relates directly to establishing rules and procedures for permit and application fees. This fits closely with "PROC_ORD_RULES," as it pertains to rules and ordinances that guide municipal laws, specifically regarding fees associated with building and zoning. Establishing such fees involves ordinance procedures and fits under the category that addresses procedural rules.','K. ORD 15-080 First Reading of an Ordinance Establishing the Annual Building and Construction Permit Fees and Zoning Application Fees of the Village of Oak Park.','be1eac76-aad2-45e4-8e99-f68b97d4a773',218,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('K. ORD 15-080 First Reading of an Ordinance Establishing the Annual Building and\nConstruction Permit Fees and Zoning Application Fees of the Village of Oak\nPark.\nVillage Manager Pavlicek stated that Items J and K are related. Item J removes\nthe Building Code Fee Schedule from the ordinance. Item K is a new ordinance\nthat is basically a new Building Code Fee Schedule. Staff has done significant\nwork in order to streamline it and make it comparable to some of the adjacent\ncommunities. The overall goal is to make sure the fees are simply covering the\ncosts of the building permit and review services.\nDirector of Development Customer Services Tammie Grossman answered\nquestions from the Board regarding how the new fees were determined.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(2635,1693,85,'ZONE_USE_COMM','ORD 15-074','ZONE_USE_COMM ZONE_USE_AMEND PROC_ORD_RULES The first choice, ZONE_USE_COMM, relates to commercial zoning issues which include special use permits for businesses and developments. The agenda item is about amending an ordinance that pertains to the commercial use of sidewalk space. This falls within the realm of how land is used commercially, making ZONE_USE_COMM the most fitting classification.','L. ORD 15-074 Second Reading and Adoption of an Ordinance Amending Chapter 22  ("Streets and Sidewalks"), Article 10 ("Commercial Use of Sidewalk Space") of the Oak Park Village Code.','ab3e844a-a53d-4304-b824-35e22a179a59',218,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('L. ORD 15-074 Second Reading and Adoption of an Ordinance Amending Chapter 22\n(“Streets and Sidewalks”), Article 10 (“Commercial Use of Sidewalk Space”)\nof the Oak Park Village Code.\nVillage Manager Pavlicek noted that some minor adjustments have been made\nin response to Board comments during the First Reading.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Brewer, seconded by Village Trustee Tucker,\nthat this Ordinance be adopted. The motion was approved. The roll call on the\nvote was as follows:\nAYES: 5 - Village Trustee Brewer, Village Trustee Ott, Village Trustee Salzman, Village\nTrustee Tucker, and Village President Abu-Taleb\nNAYS: 0\nABSENT: 2 - Village Trustee Barber, and Village Trustee Lueck\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
