INSERT INTO items VALUES(2736,7581,2335,'ENV_SUS_CLIM','ID 20-329','ENV_SUS_CLIM ECON_DEV_COMM PUB_ENG_MEET The item "Presentation on Outdoor Winter Dining Concepts for Discussion" suggests a forward-thinking approach to dining that might involve adapting to climate challenges, especially as it pertains to outdoor dining during colder months. This aligns with ENV_SUS_CLIM because it likely involves discussions about how to create sustainable and viable options for outdoor dining, considering weather and climate impacts. Furthermore, it touches upon economic development by supporting local businesses through innovative dining solutions, hence ECON_DEV_COMM as the second fit. Finally, the item could involve engaging the public or stakeholders in discussion, which falls under PUB_ENG_MEET.','G. ID 20-329 Presentation on Outdoor Winter Dining Concepts for Discussion','d6bf426c-b47f-4127-8278-8114027723e2',226,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:39:00',replace('G. ID 20-329 Presentation on Outdoor Winter Dining Concepts for Discussion\nVillage Manager provided a brief overview.\nJim Lencione presented four options for outdoor winter dining. The Village Board\ndiscussed these options and how the covid restrictions are subject to change\nper the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), Cook County and\nState of Illinois guidelines.\nStaff will look further into this presentation and come back to the Village Board\nwith further recommendations.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
