INSERT INTO items VALUES(3116,2866,1278,'TRANS_INF_TRANS','ID 18-917','TRANS_INF_TRANS TRANS_INF_EXP PUB_ENG_HEAR The primary reason for selecting TRANS_INF_TRANS as the best fit is because the agenda item concerns transportation projects, specifically the update on options for a dockless bike share program. This aligns closely with the category''s focus on public transit and transportation projects. Dockless bike share programs are a form of micro-mobility within the transportation ecosystem, making TRANS_INF_TRANS the most relevant classification for this item.','ID 18-917 Update on Options for a Dockless Bike Share Program in the Village of Oak Park','ae5aece1-eb7b-44fd-abef-44a6b7bf9d69',255,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-10-28T01:59:45',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(3117,4144,652,'TRANS_INF_PARK','ID 18-918','TRANS_INF_PARK PUB_WRK_PARK ECON_DEV_REDEV The first choice, TRANS_INF_PARK, was made because the agenda item "Unified Parking Technology Update" aligns closely with the category concerning parking lot management and parking infrastructure improvements. It matches the description of updates and discussions involving parking infrastructure, which can include technological advancements in parking systems.','ID 18-918 Unified Parking Technology Update','a9e16371-674f-4f9d-a97a-5574a96e9012',255,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('C. ID 18-918 Unified Parking Technology Update\nVillage Manger Pavlicek noted that it has been a multi-year process to update the\ntechnology. She gave an overview of old and new programs.\nMs. Grossman stated that staff did an RFP in November for a unified technology system\nfor all parking processes. Nine proposals were received and five vendors were interviewed.\nStaff will be recommending Passport Parking as the preferred vendor due to their ability to\nlink the on-street payment systems with a customized app that enables users to fulfill all\nof their parking needs in the Village. The contract will be forthcoming for approval on the\nfirst Regular Meeting in September. Staff is also looking to obtain equipment for the\npolice to provide consistency.\nVillage Trustee Andrews raised the topic of push notifications being used for advertising\nto help pay for the app.\nVillage Trustee Boutet liked that this will help eliminate the line for permits. She asked\nhow people without the app will operate. Ms. Grossman commented that the stations all\naccept cash and credit cards and there will still be staff at Village Hall to assist people.\nVillage Trustee Taglia asked what the budget for this is. Ms. Grossman gave a\nbreakdown of costs and noted that they have stayed within budget.\nMs. Grossman described how the various components of the parking operations are\nlinked.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
