INSERT INTO items VALUES(3550,118,3582,'RACE_EQ_COMM','ID 23-317','RACE_EQ_COMM STAFF_MGMT_REVIEW PUB_ENG_CITIZEN The first choice, RACE_EQ_COMM, was made because the agenda item "Cultural Competency Training Part 1" implies a focus on improving understanding and skills related to diversity and inclusion. Cultural competency training is closely aligned with community discussions and initiatives aiming to advance racial equity and diversity, which corresponds with the description of RACE_EQ_COMM.','ID 23-317 Cultural Competency Training Part 1','ee921c1e-2b34-4fb6-8486-7c4b39e19e1c',295,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:39:00',replace('A. ID 23-317 Cultural Competency Training Part 1\nVillage Manager Kevin Jackson introduced the Item.\nChief DEI Officer Dr. Danielle Walker presented Part 1 of the Cultural\nCompetency Training.\nTrustee Robinson said she would like to learn more about building together\nas a community.\nTrustee Parakkat said he would like to learn more about the timeline and\nthe right balance between looking back and looking forward. Progress has\nto be the fundamental thing and setting artificial tests in the community sets\nbarriers.\nTrustee Straw acknowledged that where we are is not perfect and where\nwe are going is to be better from here and how do we achieve that in our\ncommunity.\nPresident Scaman said she would like to continue using the listening to\nlearn approach.\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
