INSERT INTO items VALUES(3712,427,241,'ZONE_USE_PERMIT','ORD 18-446','ZONE_USE_PERMIT PROC_ORD_RULES FIN_MGT_TAX The first choice, ZONE_USE_PERMIT, was made because the agenda item specifically mentions the adoption of an ordinance that sets fees for building and construction permits as well as zoning application fees. This directly ties into special use permits for businesses and housing developments within the municipality, aligning closely with the kind of zoning-related ordinance described by ZONE_USE_PERMIT.','C. ORD 18-446 Second Reading and Adoption of an Ordinance Establishing the Annual Building and Construction Permit Fees and the Zoning Application Fees of the Village of Oak Park','f95a274c-62a7-4217-8852-a2fed7cc92f8',312,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-10-28T01:59:45',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(3713,668,228,'PUB_WRK_UTIL','ORD 18-454','PUB_WRK_UTIL PUB_HLT_SERV ENV_SUS_RECY The agenda item primarily involves amending local ordinances related to public utilities and public health - specifically, those dealing with garbage, weeds, littering, and water meter charges. The classification PUB_WRK_UTIL fits best because it refers to utility projects and public infrastructure improvements, which align well with the ordinance changes concerning water and related service charges. The aspect of garbage and waste management could also relate to public health services (PUB_HLT_SERV) and environmental sustainability efforts (ENV_SUS_RECY), but the primary focus appears to be on utility management and infrastructure, making PUB_WRK_UTIL the most relevant classification.','D. ORD 18-454 Second Reading and Adoption of An Ordinance Amending Chapter 20 ("Public Health"), Article 7 ("Garbage, Weeds and Littering") and Chapter 26 ("Water"), Article 2 ("Charges and Collections"), Section 26-2-2 ("Meter Charges") of the Oak Park Vi','17e34369-f491-437c-aeb7-b33d22b660ad',312,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('D. ORD 18-454 Second Reading and Adoption of An Ordinance Amending Chapter 20\n(“Public Health”), Article 7 (“Garbage, Weeds and Littering”) and Chapter\n26 (“Water”), Article 2 (“Charges and Collections”), Section 26-2-2 (“Meter\nCharges”) of the Oak Park Village Code Regarding Rates for Garbage,\nRefuse, Yard Waste and Recyclable Materials Collection Services\nVillage Manager Pavlicek stated that this also was on the November 5 Agenda as a First\nReading.\nDirector of Public Works John Wielebnicki explained the services included with the\nWaste Management contract. These include garbage, yard waste, leaf pick-up and the\n"At Your Door" program.\nVillage Trustee Boutet encouraged residents to compost and consider mulching leaves.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Tucker, seconded by Village Trustee Andrews,\nthat this Ordinance be adopted. The motion was approved. The roll call on the\nvote was as follows:\nAYES: 7 - Village Trustee Button, Village Trustee Taglia, Village President Abu-Taleb, Village\nTrustee Tucker, Village Trustee Moroney, Village Trustee Boutet, and Village\nTrustee Andrews\nNAYS: 0\nABSENT: 0\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
