INSERT INTO items VALUES(3733,2362,472,'TRANS_INF_TRAFFIC','MOT 19-64','TRANS_INF_TRAFFIC PUB_WRK_ROADS PUB_ENG_HEAR The agenda item "19-64 U. MOT 19-64 A Motion to Concur with the Transportation Commission''s Recommendation to Upgrade from Two-Way, East-West STOP Signs to All-Way STOP Signs at the Intersection of Adams Street and Wisconsin Avenue" primarily focuses on the modification of traffic signs at a particular intersection. The classification "TRANS_INF_TRAFFIC" is the best fit because it deals with traffic-related issues, such as the implementation of new stop signs and road safety improvements, which aligns directly with the action described in the agenda item.','U. MOT 19-64 A Motion to Concur with the Transportation Commission''s Recommendation to Upgrade from Two-Way, East-West STOP Signs to All-Way STOP Signs at the Intersection of Adams Street and Wisconsin Avenue','7cd1fe5e-7c18-4d18-8451-50bffc178eac',314,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('U. MOT 19-64 A Motion to Concur with the Transportation Commission’s\nRecommendation to Upgrade from Two-Way, East-West STOP Signs to\nAll-Way STOP Signs at the Intersection of Adams Street and Wisconsin\nAvenue\nVillage Manager Pavlicek stated that staff has received the traffic calming petition from\nresidents. Staff does not support this because it doesn''t meet the standard traffic\nwarrants in terms of crash data and traffic volume.\nMeghann Moses is a member of the Transportation Commission but also resides near\nthe intersection where the proposed signs would be installed. She stated that none of her\nneighbors knew this would be discussed tonight and would''ve liked to be present. She\ndisagrees with the Village''s policy regarding placement of stop signs. This intersection is\nnear a hospital, with high traffic speeding through, and there are children present walking\nto and from school. She doesn''t understand why other intersections with lesser concerns\nhave been upgraded to all-way stop signs.\nVillage Trustee Boutet suggested tabling the Item, as no member of the Transportation\nCommission is present to discuss their recommendation, nor are residents present to\nspeak their concerns. Village Trustee Walker-Peddakotla agreed.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Boutet, seconded by Village Trustee\nWalker-Peddakotla, that this Motion be tabled. The motion was approved. The\nroll call on the vote was as follows:\nAYES: 5 - Village President Abu-Taleb, Village Trustee Boutet, Village Trustee Buchanan,\nVillage Trustee Taglia, and Village Trustee Walker-Peddakotla\nNAYS: 2 - Village Trustee Andrews, and Village Trustee Moroney\nABSENT: 0\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(3734,2834,670,'PUB_HLT_MENT','MOT 19-77','PUB_HLT_MENT PUB_ENG_CITIZEN PUB_HLT_SERV The first choice, PUB_HLT_MENT, was made because the agenda item involves a motion related to designating the village as a "Dementia Friendly Community." This directly pertains to mental health awareness and community well-being initiatives, which aligns closely with the symbolic name PUB_HLT_MENT that focuses on mental health and community well-being.','V. MOT 19-77 A Motion to Concur with the Aging In Place Commission''s Recommendation for the Village of Oak Park to Pursue Designation as a Dementia Friendly Community','c24c4ae2-f86f-440a-a202-aa1f453c1bda',314,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-10-28T01:59:45',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(3735,3504,907,'FIN_MGT_AUDIT','MOT 19-57','FIN_MGT_AUDIT FIN_MGT_BUDGET FIN_MGT_GRANTS The agenda item "19-57 W. MOT 19-57 A Motion to Receive the Fiscal Year 2018 Comprehensive Annual Financial Report (CAFR) and Supporting Documents" is classified as FIN_MGT_AUDIT because it specifically mentions the receipt of a Comprehensive Annual Financial Report (CAFR), which is a key component of financial audits and reviews. The description for FIN_MGT_AUDIT includes annual financial audits and fiscal performance reviews, which aligns directly with the content of the agenda item, making it the most appropriate classification.','W. MOT 19-57 A Motion to Receive the Fiscal Year 2018 Comprehensive Annual Financial Report (CAFR) and Supporting Documents.','5c7eb0a5-1a91-4d07-a36d-426f81ed4bff',314,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-10-28T01:59:45',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(3736,4411,396,'FIN_MGT_BUDGET','ORD 19-41','FIN_MGT_BUDGET FIN_MGT_AUDIT FIN_MGT_GRANTS The first choice, FIN_MGT_BUDGET, was made because the agenda item specifically refers to an ordinance that involves amending the annual budget. The discussion and process of amending the fiscal year budget fall squarely within the realm of budget management and financial planning for the municipality, which aligns with the FIN_MGT_BUDGET category of budget discussions and adjustments.','X. ORD 19-41 An Ordinance Amending the Fiscal Year 2019 Annual Budget','089640e5-d40f-4a99-9c61-2b3532fd1433',314,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('X. ORD 19-41 An Ordinance Amending the Fiscal Year 2019 Annual Budget\nVillage Manager Pavlicek summarized the amendments.\nVillage Engineer Bill McKenna clarified that the reclassification of the Madison Street TIF\nfunds was due to an error in account numbers.\nVillage Trustee Buchanan asked for an explanation of the funds going to public art. Mr.\nDrazner stated that the sale of the Lake and Forest Garage allocated $40,000 to be set\naside for public art. It is currently in the Parking Fund and needs to be transferred to the\nGeneral Fund. Staff is looking for an additional $10,000 from the General Fund balance for\npublic art. Village Manager Pavlicek explained that the General Fund has an unrestricted\nbalance of $12.3 million, which can be spent as needed at the Village Board''s discretion.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Moroney, seconded by Village Trustee Boutet,\nthat this Ordinance be adopted. The motion was approved. The roll call on the\nvote was as follows:\nAYES: 7 - Village President Abu-Taleb, Village Trustee Andrews, Village Trustee Boutet,\nVillage Trustee Buchanan, Village Trustee Moroney, Village Trustee Taglia, and\nVillage Trustee Walker-Peddakotla\nNAYS: 0\nABSENT: 0\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
