INSERT INTO items VALUES(3961,3707,197,'FIN_MGT_BUDGET','ORD 15-207','FIN_MGT_BUDGET FIN_MGT_TAX FIN_MGT_GRANTS The agenda item is focused on the issuance of general obligation corporate purpose bonds and the provision for the levy and collection of a direct annual tax. This suggests a financial discussion centered on budget allocations and management, making "FIN_MGT_BUDGET" the most appropriate classification. This selection is based on the relevance of budgeting discussions typically involving the issuance of bonds and tax levies, reflecting strategic decisions on fiscal revenue and expenditure planning. The bond issuance closely relates to managing financial resources for municipal operations, aligning strongly with this category.','AY. ORD 15-207 An Ordinance Providing for the Issuance of $9,000,000 General Obligation Corporate Purpose Bonds, Series 2015B, of the Village of Oak Park, Cook County, Illinois, and Providing for the Levy and Collection of a Direct Annual Tax for the Payme','f6173794-86cf-4fbe-89db-76e5ac0af3b1',331,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('AY. ORD 15-207 An Ordinance Providing for the Issuance of $9,000,000 General Obligation\nCorporate Purpose Bonds, Series 2015B, of the Village of Oak Park, Cook\nCounty, Illinois, and Providing for the Levy and Collection of a Direct\nAnnual Tax for the Payment of the Principal of and Interest on Said Bonds.\nVillage Manager Pavlicek stated that this would fund the first two years of the streets and\nalleyway program as well as additional funding for the street lighting project along the\nHarrison Street Business District and some of the cost associated with the CityView\nsoftware implementation.\nChief Financial Officer Craig Lesner added that the interest rate is 3.46%.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Tucker, seconded by Village Trustee Brewer,\nthat this Ordinance be adopted. The motion was approved. The roll call on the\nvote was as follows:\nAYES: 7 - Village Trustee Barber, Village Trustee Brewer, Village Trustee Lueck, Village\nTrustee Ott, Village Trustee Salzman, Village Trustee Tucker, and Village President\nAbu-Taleb\nNAYS: 0\nABSENT: 0\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(3962,3904,168,'FIN_MGT_BUDGET','ORD 15-217','FIN_MGT_BUDGET FIN_MGT_AUDIT FIN_MGT_TAX The first choice, FIN_MGT_BUDGET, was selected because the agenda item is primarily concerned with financial management activities that involve surplus revenue from the environmental services and parking funds being transferred to the general fund. This indicates a specific focus on the allocation and distribution of revenues within the budgetary framework of the fiscal year. The declaration of surplus and authorization of fund transfers are typical components of budget discussions and fiscal management.','AZ. ORD 15-217 An Ordinance Declaring Surplus Revenue in the Village of Oak Park''s Environmental Services Fund and Parking Fund for the 2015 Fiscal Year and Authorizing the Distribution and Transfer of those Surplus Revenues to the Village''s General Fund','1dd7e913-6f5f-448e-bb2b-5ca6e4471fac',331,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-10-28T01:59:45',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(3963,4072,148,'FIN_MGT_BUDGET','ORD 15-223','FIN_MGT_BUDGET FIN_MGT_AUDIT FIN_MGT_GRANTS The first choice, FIN_MGT_BUDGET, was made because the agenda item specifically mentions an ordinance amending a fiscal year budget. This directly relates to budget discussions and adjustments for the specified fiscal year, fitting well with the category that involves detailed budget breakdowns and amendments.','BA. ORD 15-223 An Ordinance Amending the Fiscal Year 2015 Budget.','a86a726e-25f0-45a5-a4c1-245138f26167',331,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('BA. ORD 15-223 An Ordinance Amending the Fiscal Year 2015 Budget.\nVillage Manager Pavlicek noted that at the end of each fiscal year, an updated overall\nbudget is adopted. This will allow the auditors to start preliminary work on the annual\nfiscal audit by ensuring that all legislative documents and actions are current.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Tucker, seconded by Village Trustee Brewer,\nthat this Ordinance be adopted. The motion was approved. The roll call on the\nvote was as follows:\nAYES: 7 - Village Trustee Barber, Village Trustee Brewer, Village Trustee Lueck, Village\nTrustee Ott, Village Trustee Salzman, Village Trustee Tucker, and Village President\nAbu-Taleb\nNAYS: 0\nABSENT: 0\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(3964,4220,116,'FIN_MGT_TAX','ORD 15-204','FIN_MGT_TAX FIN_MGT_BUDGET PROC_ORD_RULES The agenda item "15-204 BB. ORD 15-204 The Village of Oak Park''s 2015 Property Tax Levy Ordinance" is best classified under "FIN_MGT_TAX" because it specifically refers to a property tax levy ordinance. This categorization is focused on tax-related ordinances and fiscal management, which aligns precisely with the description of financial management related to tax levy ordinances and ensuring adequate funding for municipal services. The mention of a "tax levy" is a strong indicator that it pertains to taxation, thus making FIN_MGT_TAX the most appropriate classification.','BB. ORD 15-204 The Village of Oak Park''s 2015 Property Tax Levy Ordinance','06d9ccfb-cbeb-41c2-8d1b-fb2253e7c550',331,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('BB. ORD 15-204 The Village of Oak Park’s 2015 Property Tax Levy Ordinance\nVillage Manager Pavlicek stated that the property tax levy funds the General Fund, Police\nand Firemen''s Pension Funds, as well as the Library in accordance with their request\nmade to the Village.\nVillage Trustee Lueck stated that it is worth mentioning that the Library''s levy is down,\nand they are committed to not raising it back.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Barber, seconded by Village Trustee Salzman,\nthat this Ordinance be adopted. The motion was approved. The roll call on the\nvote was as follows:\nAYES: 7 - Village Trustee Barber, Village Trustee Brewer, Village Trustee Lueck, Village\nTrustee Ott, Village Trustee Salzman, Village Trustee Tucker, and Village President\nAbu-Taleb\nNAYS: 0\nABSENT: 0\n','\n',char(10)),NULL);
