INSERT INTO items VALUES(4018,4000,170,'FIN_MGT_AUDIT','MOT 18-327','FIN_MGT_AUDIT FIN_MGT_BUDGET FIN_MGT_TAX The first choice, FIN_MGT_AUDIT, was made because the agenda item involves the approval of a financial report. The term "Unaudited Year-to-Date Quarterly Financial Report" closely relates to the annual financial audits and reviews of fiscal performance as described in the classification for FIN_MGT_AUDIT. The focus on financial reporting fits the classification that deals specifically with financial audits and reviews rather than broader budget discussions or tax-related issues.','Z. MOT 18-327 A Motion to Approve the Unaudited Year-to-Date Quarterly Financial Report as of March 31, 2018','ef810a8f-92c2-425b-b55c-8b4d62d27bbc',334,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-10-28T01:59:45',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO items VALUES(4019,4170,228,'FIN_MGT_BUDGET','MOT 18-325','FIN_MGT_BUDGET FIN_MGT_AUDIT FIN_MGT_TAX The agenda item "18-325 R. MOT 18-325 A Motion to Approve the April 2018 Monthly Treasurer''s Report for All Funds" is best classified under "FIN_MGT_BUDGET" because it relates to financial management, specifically focusing on the budget. The Treasurer''s Report involves reviewing and approving a comprehensive financial document that typically details revenue and expenditures for the municipality, which is essential for budgetary decisions. This aligns closely with discussions on budgets and financial reviews indicated by the "FIN_MGT_BUDGET" category description.','R. MOT 18-325 A Motion to Approve the April 2018 Monthly Treasurer''s Report for All Funds','a919370f-0a3c-43c7-841c-356adbc71c31',334,'2024-10-28T01:59:45','2024-11-05T04:38:59',replace('R. MOT 18-325 A Motion to Approve the April 2018 Monthly Treasurer’s Report for All\nFunds\nVillage Trustee Boutet stated that when the Board gets the monthly Treasurer''s Report, it\nwould be helpful if the CFO did a presentation regarding general trends.\nChief Financial Officer Steve Drazner stated that this report includes the April 2018\nbalance compared to the March 2018 balance and the April 2017 balance. The reason for\nsome of the major variances from last year to this year is due to the change in\naccounting software. The new software is more efficient and reflects actual cash balances\non funds.\nVillage Manager Pavlicek stated that this is required by State Statute and she and CFO\nDrazner agree that this should be discussed every month.\nMr. Drazner answered questions from the Board and heard their comments.\nIt was moved by Village Trustee Tucker, seconded by Village TrusteeTaglia, that\nthis Motion be approved. A voice vote was taken and the motion was approved.\n','\n',char(10)),1);
